==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Styphnic
<hw>Styph"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. (spurious)
<grk>sty`fein</grk> to contract.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a yellow crystalline astringent
acid, <chform>(NO2)3.C6H.(OH)2</chform>, obtained by the action of
nitric acid on resorcin. <xex>Styphnic acid</xex> resembles picric acid,
but is not bitter. It acts like a strong dibasic acid, having a series
of well defined salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Styptic</ent>⟦br⟧
